The paper deals with modelling artificial neural networks and their ability to form robust associative memories. This topic falls under the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Hebbian learning, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with the principles of energy usage and network interference, which are relevant to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of connections and processing of inputs, which are relevant to the sub-category of Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
